latestIgtvVideos.title: What’s the difference? Seasonings vs Rubs vs. Marinades vs. Brines
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Que & A: Seasonings, Rubs, Marinades & Brines – What’s the difference? #GrillTips

In a nutshell… 
SEASONINGS are dried herbs & spices that help to flavor a dish before or after cooking. 

RUBS are combos of spices, salt & sugar that add flavor and texture before cooking. 

MARINADES are blends of oil, vinegar, spices & herbs that infuse flavor before cooking. 

BRINES (at least wet brines) are used to infuse flavor and moisture before cooking. 

What are your favorite ways to add flavor?
